Patient: What kind of exercise should I do for my heart condition? 

Healthcare Educator: Start with light activities like walking, slowly increase the pace as you feel comfortable.

Patient: How long should I walk each day?

Healthcare Educator: Aim for 30 minutes daily. You can split it into shorter sessions if that's easier.

Patient: What if I get tired during the exercise?

Healthcare Educator: Listen to your body. If you feel tired, take a break. Over time, your endurance will improve.

Patient: Is there any other exercise I can do?

Healthcare Educator: Yes, activities like cycling or swimming are also good. Remember, start slow and gradually increase intensity.

Patient: What if I don't feel like exercising some days?

Healthcare Educator: That's okay. Everyone has those days. Try to get back on track as soon as you can.